In a message dated 7/8/03 9:10:27 PM Central Daylight Time, 
Proudwing500k@... writes:


&gt; Tyrael: Then your challenge is accepted, Maxima! Come and do your worst.
&gt; 
&gt; He fired a wide beam of concentrated light at her face, trying to
&gt; blind her and overwhelm her optics.

The light blinded her for a moment, &quot;Aaahhhhhh!!&quot; as she cringed back a 
moment, then regained herself as she barely caught sight of him & started towards 
him.

&gt; 
&gt; Tyrael: So, you really think Alpha Trion has waken you for you to live
&gt; free? He might be Autobot, but the old geezer is no fool. You are
&gt; there for a purpose. Even the Tripredacus Council knew that!

Again, she growled at him. Alpha Trion was one of those she loathed. He was 
one of those responsible or so she tagged, for the demise of her mentor... & 
one of Megatron&#39;s creators... Gamma Quadran. 

&quot;I belong to no one,&quot; she growled at Tyrael. &quot;Least of all Alpha Trion!&quot;

As to a plan that was in store for her.. she didn&#39;t care. She made her own 
destiny. & as long as the Decepticons were a major part of it. 

&gt; 
&gt; He turned to Hydras.
&gt; 
&gt; Tyrael: By the way, Hydras, did you know that we were the ones
&gt; manipulating the Predacons all along?

She didn&#39;t wait for Hydras&#39; response to him. She wanted this Tripred so 
terribly, to feel his life fluids dripping through her claws after she ripped him 
apart.

She charged at him with her saber ready to strike. &quot;Best beg to Primus, you 
will NEED it!&quot; she growled in hate & loathing. Pure evil dripping from her 
voice as her crimson optics glowed. Despite her damage, she went on. She had to, 
she must. 

Swinging her saber hard at his neck, the other ready to jab at his midsection 
or block if needed. 

